Must-Have (A):

RA001 : There should be a main menu.
RA001a : The main menu should contain a "Start Button", which loades the main scene on click.
RA001b : The main menu should contain an "Exit Button", which terminates the game on click.
RA002 : There is an environment for the player to drive around.
RA003 : The Player character, represented by a tank, is being displayed on screen.
RA004 : The Player has to be able to move by using WASD.
RA005 : The Player is able to shoot by pressing Spacebar. 
RA006 : The game should have some sort of physics (eg. The bullet flys in a realistic way, the Player falls into holes).
RA007 : The game should have some sort of coolision detection (eg. The bullet collides with enemies and explodes)

Should-Be (B):

RB101 : Every implemented requirement must be blackbox-tested with a corresponding test-document(ation).
RB002 : The main menu should contain an "Options Button", which opens the options menu on click. (Requires RA001)
RB002a : The volume should be able to be changed.

Nice-To-Have (C):

RC201 : The bullet have an explosion effect on impact.
RC202 : The tank canon should emit a particle effect each time it shoots.
